      "text": "Here\u0027s the accurate English translation of the provided Maldivian text:\n\n**Laws of the Maldives**\n\n**Law on the Gifting or Selling of Private Property of Individuals Registered with the Government**\n\n**(Including the 1st Amendment to this Law)**\n\n**Law on the Gifting or Selling of Private Property of Individuals Registered with the Government**\n\nThe gifting or selling of private property belonging to individuals registered with the government shall only be permitted after the relevant authorities have ascertained whether there is any outstanding debt owed to the government or government-related parties, whether by way of loan or otherwise. Furthermore, it will be permitted only after the Ministry of Justice and Islamic Affairs, the Ministry of Public Safety, and the High Court of the Maldives have verified if there is any proven debt owed to private parties. The proceeds from the sale of such property shall first be used to settle any outstanding amounts owed to the parties mentioned above, in proportion to the amount each party is owed.\n\nLaw Number: 28/76\nCommencement Date: 27 November 1976\nAmendment Number: 1\n\nCopyright © 2023 Attorney General\u0027s Office.",
